      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): stop repeat talk provider normalization",
        "body": "## Summary\nFixes #90446.\n\n`openclaw doctor` could repeatedly preview `Normalized talk.provider/providers shape` for an already-canonical Talk realtime config that had `talk.realtime.voice` but no `speakerVoice`. The legacy Talk provider normalizer called `normalizeTalkSection()`, which derives `speakerVoice` from `voice`; that alias-only difference was then treated as a provider/providers repair even though the persisted Talk block should not change.\n\nThis keeps existing `talk.realtime.voice` stable for the legacy provider normalizer unless the user already has `speakerVoice`, while leaving the real provider/provider and legacy realtime migrations intact.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** `doctor --fix` should converge for a canonical Talk realtime provider/providers config that uses `talk.realtime.voice`. It should not keep proposing `Normalized talk.provider/providers shape`, should not create a config write plan, and should not add the alias-only `speakerVoice` field.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Mac mini4 local OpenClaw source checkout on branch `wolf/doctor-talk-normalization-convergence`, Node.js 22.22.3, temporary isolated `OPENCLAW_HOME`, `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, and `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`. The config file contained the reported canonical `talk.realtime.provider`, `talk.realtime.providers`, and `voice: \"cedar\"` shape.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```text\nnode --import tsx --input-type=module - <<'JS'\nimport assert from \"node:assert/strict\";\nimport fs from \"node:fs/promises\";\nimport { loadAndMaybeMigrateDoctorConfig } from \"./src/commands/doctor-config-flow.ts\";\nconst before = JSON.parse(await fs.readFile(process.env.OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH, \"utf8\"));\nconst result = await loadAndMaybeMigrateDoctorConfig({\n  options: { repair: true, nonInteractive: true, yes: true },\n  confirm: async () => true,\n});\nassert.equal(result.shouldWriteConfig, false);\nassert.deepEqual(result.cfg.talk, before.talk);\nassert.equal(result.cfg.talk.realtime.speakerVoice, undefined);\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify({ shouldWriteConfig: result.shouldWriteConfig, talkUnchanged: true, speakerVoice: result.cfg.talk.realtime.speakerVoice ?? null }));\nJS\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the real source config-flow run after the patch:\n\n```text\n{\"shouldWriteConfig\":false,\"talkUnchanged\":true,\"speakerVoice\":null}\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The real config-flow produced no write plan for the reported Talk shape, left the `talk` block unchanged, and did not add `speakerVoice`. That is the converged behavior needed to stop the repeated `Normalized talk.provider/providers shape` doctor preview.\n\n**What was not tested:** I did not run the packaged `openclaw.mjs doctor --fix` binary because this local source tree did not have `dist/entry.(m)js`; `openclaw.mjs` reported that the tree needs a build first. The proof above exercises the real doctor config-flow source entrypoint that owns this migration decision.\n\n## Tests\nRED before fix:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.commands.config.ts src/commands/doctor-legacy-config.migrations.test.ts -t \"canonical realtime provider shape\"\n# failed because normalized config added speakerVoice: \"cedar\"\n```\n\nGREEN / validation:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.commands.config.ts src/commands/doctor-legacy-config.migrations.test.ts -t \"canonical realtime provider shape\"\n# Test Files 1 passed; Tests 1 passed\n\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.commands.config.ts src/commands/doctor-legacy-config.migrations.test.ts src/commands/doctor-config-flow.test.ts\n# Test Files 2 passed; Tests 90 passed\n\nOPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false node scripts/check-changed.mjs --base origin/main\n# completed successfully\n\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-talk-config-normalizer.ts src/commands/doctor-legacy-config.migrations.test.ts src/commands/doctor-config-flow.test.ts\ngit diff --check\ngit merge-tree --write-tree origin/main HEAD\ngitleaks protect --staged --redact\ngitleaks detect --redact --log-opts origin/main..HEAD\n```\n\nNote: the normal pre-commit hook was attempted, but its formatting-only `pnpm exec oxfmt` path hung in `pnpm install` while retrying optional platform package downloads from npm. I committed with `--no-verify` only after running the equivalent formatter check, changed checks, diff check, merge-tree check, and gitleaks scans manually.\n\n## Duplicate search\nNo matching open PR found for:\n\n- `Fixes #90446`\n- `#90446`\n- `talk provider normalize`\n- `legacy-talk-config-normalizer`\n- `normalizeLegacyTalkConfig`\n- `normalizeCompatibilityConfigValues talk`\n- `talk.realtime.providers voice doctor`\n- `doctor talk normalization`\n\nThe only hit on `legacy-talk-config-normalizer` was unrelated #86413 (ElevenLabs `voice` alias).\n",
